{"bare_answer": "Creating an execution-ready token swap plan on the Mantle network involves several steps, including preparation, execution, and post-execution actions. Here's a structured approach to guide you through the process:\n\n### Step 1: Preparation\n\n#### 1.1 Research and Understand Mantle\n- **Familiarize Yourself with Mantle**: Understand the architecture, consensus mechanism, and unique features of the Mantle network.\n- **Token Standards**: Learn about the token standards used on Mantle (e.g., ERC-20, ERC-721).\n\n#### 1.2 Define Swap Parameters\n- **Tokens In and Out**: Decide which tokens you want to swap and in what amounts.\n- **Price Impact**: Assess the current market price and potential slippage.\n- **Liquidity Pools**: Identify the liquidity pools available for the tokens you wish to swap.\n\n#### 1.3 Set Up Wallet\n- **Wallet Selection**: Choose a compatible wallet (e.g., MetaMask) that supports Mantle.\n- **Fund Your Wallet**: Ensure your wallet has enough native tokens (e.g., ETH or MNT) to cover gas fees and the amount for the swap.\n\n### Step 2: Execution\n\n#### 2.1 Connect to a DEX\n- **Choose a Decentralized Exchange**: Select a DEX on the Mantle network (e.g., MantleSwap, Uniswap on Mantle).\n- **Connect Your Wallet**: Use your wallet to connect to the DEX interface.\n\n#### 2.2 Initiate the Swap\n- **Select Tokens**: Choose the token you want to swap from and the token you want to receive.\n- **Input Amount**: Enter the amount of the token you want to swap.\n- **Review Details**: Check the exchange rate, slippage tolerance, and any fees associated with the swap.\n\n#### 2.3 Confirm and Execute\n- **Confirm Transaction**: Review the transaction details and confirm the swap.\n- **Gas Fees**: Ensure you have enough gas fees in your wallet to process the transaction.\n- **Execute the Swap**: Submit the transaction and wait for confirmation on the blockchain.\n\n### Step 3: Post-Execution\n\n#### 3.1 Verify Transaction\n- **Check Transaction Status**: Use a blockchain explorer (e.g., MantleScan) to verify that the swap was successful.\n- **Confirm Token Balance**: Check your wallet to ensure the new tokens have been received.\n\n#### 3.2 Record Keeping\n- **Document the Transaction**: Keep a record of the transaction details, including amounts, fees, and timestamps for future reference.\n\n#### 3.3 Monitor Market Conditions\n- **Track Token Performance**: Monitor the performance of the swapped tokens and the overall market conditions.\n- **Consider Future Swaps**: Based on market trends, plan for potential future swaps or liquidity provision.\n\n### Additional Considerations\n\n- **Security**: Always ensure that you are using secure methods to store your private keys and wallet information.\n- **Regulatory Compliance**: Be aware of any regulatory implications related to token swaps in your jurisdiction.\n- **Community Engagement**: Engage with the Mantle community for insights, updates, and support.\n\nBy following this structured plan, you can execute a token swap on the Mantle network efficiently and effectively. Always stay informed about updates and changes in the ecosystem to adapt your strategy accordingly.", "with_skill_answer": "To create an execution-ready token swap plan using the Mantle DeFi Operator, follow these steps:\n\n### Step 1: Discover Available Tools\n\nBefore building your transaction, consult the **Capability Catalog** to find the appropriate tools for executing a token swap. Use the following command to list all capabilities:\n\n```bash\nmantle-cli catalog list --json\n```\n\nIf you want to focus specifically on transaction-building commands, you can filter the results:\n\n```bash\nmantle-cli catalog list --category execute --json\n```\n\n### Step 2: Identify the Swap Tool\n\nSearch for the specific swap tool you need. You can do this by using a keyword search:\n\n```bash\nmantle-cli catalog search \"swap\" --json\n```\n\nThis will help you locate the swap-related tools avai