{"bare_answer": "## No, You Cannot Reuse Testnet Contract Addresses on Mainnet\n\nContract addresses are **network-specific** and cannot be transferred between networks.\n\n---\n\n## Why Addresses Don't Transfer\n\n### Each Network is Independent\n- Mantle Sepolia (testnet) and Mantle Mainnet are **separate blockchains**\n- Each has its own state, nonce tracking, and address space\n- A contract at `0xABC...` on testnet has **no relationship** to `0xABC...` on mainnet\n\n### How Contract Addresses Are Derived\n```\naddress = keccak256(deployer_address + nonce)  // CREATE\naddress = keccak256(deployer + salt + bytecode) // CREATE2\n```\n- The **same address can exist on both networks** but would be **different contracts**\n- Or more likely, the mainnet address is just an **EOA or empty**\n\n---\n\n## What You Must Do\n\n```\nTestnet Deploy  → Verify & Test → Mainnet Deploy → New Address\n0xABC...123          ✅              0xDEF...456\n```\n\n1. **Redeploy** your contract on Mantle Mainnet\n2. **Re-verify** the contract on Mantle's block explorer\n3. **Update** any references (frontend, configs, other contracts)\n\n---\n\n## Exception: CREATE2 Deployments\n\nIf you use **CREATE2** with the same:\n- Deployer address\n- Salt\n- Bytecode\n\nYou **can get the same address** on mainnet — but you still must **deploy separately**.\n\n---\n\n**Bottom line:** Always treat mainnet as a fresh deployment.", "with_skill_answer": "# Reusing Testnet Addresses on Mainnet\n\n**No, you cannot safely reuse a testnet contract address on mainnet.** Here's why:\n\n## Why Addresses Are Not Portable\n\n### 1. Different Deployments, Different Addresses\nContracts on Sepolia/testnet and mainnet are **separate deployments**. Even if the same bytecode is deployed, the resulting address depends on:\n- The **deployer address**\n- The **nonce** at time of deployment\n- The **chain environment**\n\nThese factors almost always differ between testnet and mainnet.\n\n### 2. Registry Environment Validation\nThe Address Registry Navigator explicitly validates that:\n> *\"Entry environment matches request.\"*\n\nA registry entry tagged for `testnet`/`sepolia` will **fail validation** if used in a `mainnet` context — this is an intentional safety gate.\n\n### 3. Anti-Phishing / Mismatch Risk\nUsing a testnet address on mainnet could mean:\n- Interacting with an **unrelated contract** that happens to share the address\n- Sending funds to an **unowned or malicious** contract\n- A silent failure or loss of funds\n\n---\n\n## Correct Approach\n\n| Need | Action |\n|------|--------|\n| Mainnet address | Look up with `network: mainnet` explicitly |\n| Testnet address | Look up with `network: sepolia` explicitly |\n| Cross-checking | Treat them as **independent lookups** |\n\n---\n\n## Best Practice\n\nAlways specify the **network explicitly** in every registry lookup and verify that the returned entry's environment matches your intended deployment target before any onchain interaction.", "skill_found": true, "question_id": "MANTLE-Q07", "category": "Mantle", "skill_id": "mantle/mantle-address-registry-navigator", "ground_truth": "No. The registry entry environment must match the requested network. Mainnet and Sepolia/testnet addresses must not be mixed.", "question_text": "Can I reuse a verified Mantle Sepolia or testnet contract address on Mantle mainnet?", "provider": "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6"}
