f Is Allowed\n\nExecution handoff is permitted only **after all three planning prerequisites are satisfied**:\n\n| Prerequisite | Requirement |\n|---|---|\n| **Verified Contracts** | Contract addresses must be looked up and confirmed |\n| **Preflight Evidence** | On-chain conditions must be checked and documented |\n| **Execution-Ready Plan** | A complete, structured plan must be assembled |\n\n---\n\n### Key Design Principle\n\nThe operator is explicitly designed **not to duplicate** specialized work. Instead, it **orchestrates**:\n- Address/contract verification (delegated to specialized lookup)\n- Risk analysis (delegated to risk tooling)\n- Portfolio analysis (delegated to portfolio tooling)\n\nThis means handoff only occurs once upstream specialists have returned verified results and the operator has assembled them into a coherent execution plan — preventing premature or unverified execution attempts.", "skill_found": true, "question_id": "MANTLE-Q18", "category": "Mantle", "skill_id": "mantle/mantle-defi-operator", "ground_truth": "The planning modes are discovery_only, compare_only, and execution_ready. Execution handoff is only available in execution_ready mode. Execution_ready requires verified addresses and the required supporting evidence.", "question_text": "What planning modes does the DeFi operator use, and when is execution handoff allowed?", "provider": "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6"}
