-amount <AMOUNT> \\\n  --recipient <YOUR_WALLET_ADDR> \\\n  --json\n```\n\n**Key preflight checks to verify in the response:**\n| Check | What to Confirm |\n|---|---|\n| Contract address | Matches verified registry, not a text-extracted address |\n| Token addresses | Both input and output tokens resolve correctly |\n| Slippage / price impact | Within acceptable range for your trade size |\n| Route | Confirm the swap path (direct vs. multi-hop) |\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3: Token Approval (if ERC-20 input)\n\nIf you're swapping **from an ERC-20 token** (not native MNT), you must approve the DEX router to spend your tokens first.\n\n```bash\n# Build the unsigned approval transaction\nmantle-cli swap approve \\\n  --token <TOKEN_IN> \\\n  --json\n```\n\n> ⚠️ **Critical:** Do NOT add a `from` field to this unsigned transaction. This breaks Privy and other signers. The CLI output is ready to sign as-is.\n\n**Approval transaction checklist:**\n- [ ] Spender address is the verified DEX router (from catalog, not manually extracted)\n- [ ] Amount approved matches your intended swap amount (or use max approval intentionally)\n- [ ] Sign and broadcast this transaction **before** proceeding to the swap\n\n---\n\n## Phase 4: Build the Swap Transaction\n\nOnce the approval is confirmed on-chain, build the swap:\n\n```bash\nmantle-cli swap build-swap \\\n  --provider <dex> \\\n  --in <TOKEN_IN> \\\n  --out <TOKEN_OUT> \\\n  --amount <AMOUNT> \\\n  --recipient <YOUR_WALLET_ADDR> \\\n  --json\n```\n\n**What the CLI guarantees for you:**\n- ✅ Correct calldata with verified ABI encoding\n- ✅ Verified contract", "skill_found": true, "question_id": "MANTLE-Q23", "category": "Mantle", "skill_id": "mantle/mantle-defi-operator", "ground_truth": "Normalize the swap intent and run the DeFi pre-execution guardrails first. Resolve verified router or quoter contracts through mantle-address-registry-navigator. Use curated defaults and eligible live-signal ranking before choosing a route. Pull risk evi