nId, chainId);\n  }\n  \n  // Step 2: Confirm chain is producing blocks\n  const block = await provider.getBlock(\"latest\");\n  if (!block) {\n    throw new ChainUnresponsiveError(chainId);\n  }\n  \n  // Step 3: Confirm block is recent\n  const blockAge = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000) - block.timestamp;\n  if (blockAge > CHAIN_CONFIG[chainId].maxBlockAge) {\n    throw new ChainStaleError(chainId, blockAge);\n  }\n  \n  return {\n    chainId,\n    blockNumber: block.number,\n    blockTimestamp: block.timestamp,\n    rpcUrl: provider.connection?.url ?? \"unknown\",\n  };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Usage Before Balance/Allowance Queries\n\n```typescript\nclass PortfolioAnalyst {\n  \n  async getTokenBalance(\n    tokenAddress: string,\n    walletAddress: string,\n    chainId: number", "with_skill_answer": "Based on the documentation, the portfolio analyst confirms chain context and chain status in **Step 2** by running these two commands:\n\n- **`mantle-cli chain info --json`** — retrieves chain context information\n- **`mantle-cli chain status --json`** — retrieves the current chain status\n\nThese are executed alongside a registry address validation (`mantle-cli registry validate <address> --json`) as part of the validation step, and all three must complete **before** the analyst proceeds to determine analysis scope (Step 3) or fetch any balances or allowances (Steps 4+).", "skill_found": true, "question_id": "MANTLE-Q38", "category": "Mantle", "skill_id": "mantle/mantle-portfolio-analyst", "ground_truth": "Use mantle_getChainInfo to confirm the requested network context. Use mantle_getChainStatus when available.", "question_text": "How does the portfolio analyst confirm chain context and chain status before querying balances or allowances?", "provider": "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6"}
