r your wallet or reach out to their support team for assistance.\n\nBy checking these areas, you should be able to identify the cause of the discrepancies in your Mantle wallet balance.", "with_skill_answer": "When your Mantle wallet balance differs between reads, the Mantle Readonly Debugger should follow these steps:\n\n1. **Capture Failure Context**:\n   - Record the method/tool name you are using to check the balance.\n   - Note the endpoint being accessed.\n   - Document the parameters used in the request.\n   - Include the timestamp (UTC) of when the balance was checked.\n   - Capture the full error text/code, if any error was returned.\n\n2. **Classify Error**:\n   - This situation likely falls under \"balance/nonce inconsistency.\" Ensure to classify it accordingly.\n\n3. **Run Targeted Checks**:\n   - Refer to `references/troubleshooting-playbook.md` for specific checks related to balance discrepancies. This may include verifying the RPC connection, checking for pending transactions that could affect the balance, or ensuring that the wallet is correctly synced with the blockchain.\n\n4. **Return Root-Cause Hypothesis**:\n   - Based on the checks, provide a hypothesis regarding the cause of the discrepancy and suggest immediate next steps. For example, if the issue is due to a pending transaction, recommend waiting for it to be confirmed.\n\n5. **If Unresolved, Return Bounded Escalation Checklist**:\n   - If the issue remains unresolved after the checks, prepare an escalation checklist that includes all the captured context and findings to facilitate further investigation.\n\nBy following these steps, you can systematically diagnose and address the issue of differing wallet balances.", "skill_found": true, "question_id": "MANTLE-Q43", "category": "Mantle", "skill_id": "mantle/mantle-readonly-debugger", "ground_truth": "Compare reads at latest versus pending. Check for unconfirmed transactions or nonce conflicts. Re-read at a consistent block context after a 