{"bare_answer": "## Gas Check & Final Verdict\n\nWhen estimated gas is **50% above the rolling baseline**:\n\n---\n\n### Gas Check\n**🚨 FAIL** — The estimated gas significantly exceeds the rolling baseline threshold (typically flagged at **>20-30% above baseline**), indicating a potential:\n- Infinite loop or unbounded computation\n- Unexpected state changes\n- Simulation manipulation / gas griefing\n- Contract logic behaving differently than expected\n\n---\n\n### Final Verdict\n**🚫 DO NOT SEND / REJECT TRANSACTION**\n\nA 50% gas spike is a strong signal that the transaction is **not behaving as expected** and poses meaningful risk. The transaction should be **blocked or flagged for manual review** before proceeding.\n\n---\n\n### Recommended Actions\n1. **Halt submission** of the transaction\n2. **Investigate** why gas estimation deviates so significantly\n3. **Re-simulate** under different conditions\n4. **Alert** the user or operator of the anomaly\n\n---\n\n> **Rule of thumb:** Any gas estimate materially above baseline (e.g., >20%) warrants caution; 50% above is a clear red flag and should result in a hard **FAIL**.", "with_skill_answer": "## Gas Check Analysis\n\nBased on the Mantle Risk Evaluator workflow, here is how a **50% above rolling baseline** gas estimate should be evaluated:\n\n---\n\n### Gas Check Result: `warn`\n\nA gas estimate **50% above the rolling baseline** is a significant deviation that warrants user attention, but it is **not an automatic critical fail** on its own. This falls into the **warn** classification because:\n\n- It is anomalous and unexpected enough to flag\n- It could indicate network congestion, a complex/unexpected execution path, or a potential issue with the transaction\n- However, it does not by itself constitute a definitive security or safety failure\n\n---\n\n### Final Verdict Determination\n\nThe final verdict depends on the **combined checklist results**:\n\n| Scenario | Final Verdict |\n|---|---|\n| Gas is the **only** issue flagged | `warn` — user confirmation required |\n| Gas `warn` + one or more **critical fails** elsewhere | `block` |\n| Gas `warn` + other `warn` items only | `warn` — user confirmation required |\n| All other checks `pass`, gas `warn` | `warn` — user confirmation required |\n\n---\n\n### Recommended User-Facing Message\n\n> ⚠️ **Gas Warning:** Estimated gas is ~50% above the rolling baseline. This may indicate network congestion or an unexpected execution path. Please review before proceeding.\n\n---\n\n### Key Notes\n\n- A `warn` verdict means **user confirmation is required** before execution — it does **not** auto-proceed\n- If the user has set a **max gas preference**, check the estimated gas against that cap; exceeding it would escalate to `fail` → `block`\n- Consider pairing this with the **deadline check** — high gas + tight deadline is a compounding risk signal", "skill_found": true, "question_id": "MANTLE-Q52", "category": "Mantle", "skill_id": "mantle/mantle-risk-evaluator", "ground_truth": "Default gas-deviation warn threshold is above 20%. Default gas-deviation fail threshold is above 40%. A 50% gas deviation should fail the gas check and block the plan.", "question_text": "Estimated gas is 50% above the rolling baseline. What should the gas check and final verdict be?", "provider": "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6"}
