erformance metrics for the deployed application, which can be used for future comparisons and performance tuning.\n\n11. **Stakeholder Communication**: \n    - Document any communications with stakeholders regarding the deployment, including announcements, release notes, and any training provided.\n\n12. **Post-Deployment Review**: \n    - Conduct a post-deployment review meeting and document the outcomes, including lessons learned and any identified areas for improvement.\n\nBy capturing this evidence, you create a comprehensive record of the deployment process, which can be invaluable for future reference, audits, and continuous improvement efforts.", "with_skill_answer": "After an external Mantle deployment succeeds, the following evidence should be captured and persisted:\n\n1. **Receipt Metadata**: This includes transaction hash, block number, and any relevant logs or events emitted during the deployment.\n2. **Deployment Evidence**: Any documentation or artifacts that confirm the successful deployment of the smart contract, such as deployment logs or confirmations from the external executor.\n3. **Gas Usage Information**: Details on the gas used for the deployment, including any limits that were set and the actual gas consumed.\n4. **Deployment Package**: The unsigned deployment payload and any instructions provided to the external executor for reference.\n5. **Timestamp**: The date and time when the deployment was executed.\n\nThis evidence is crucial for verification and auditing purposes, ensuring that all aspects of the deployment are documented.", "skill_found": true, "question_id": "MANTLE-Q57", "category": "Mantle", "skill_id": "mantle/mantle-smart-contract-deployer", "ground_truth": "Capture the transaction receipt or equivalent deployment evidence. Capture the deployed contract address and block number. Gas used and fee evidence are also part of the deployment report.", "question_text": "What evidence should be captured after an external Mantle deployment succeeds?", "provider": "openai/gpt-4o-mini"}
{"bare_answer": "# Verifying a Mantle Contract on the Explorer After External Deployment\n\n## Overview\n\nWhen deploying contracts externally (e.g., via Hardhat, Foundry, or manual deployment), you need to verify them on the Mantle Explorer separately.\n\n---\n\n## Method 1: Hardhat Verification\n\n### Setup `hardhat.config.js`\n\n```javascript\nrequire(\"@nomicfoundation/hardhat-verify\");\n\nmodule.exports = {\n  networks: {\n    mantle: {\n      url: \"https://rpc.mantle.xyz\",\n      chainId: 5000,\n      accounts: [process.env.PRIVATE_KEY],\n    },\n    mantleSepolia: {\n      url: \"https://rpc.sepolia.mantle.xyz\",\n      chainId: 5003,\n      accounts: [process.env.PRIVATE_KEY],\n    },\n  },\n  etherscan: {\n    apiKey: {\n      mantle: process.env.MANTLE_EXPLORER_API_KEY,\n      mantleSepolia: process.env.MANTLE_EXPLORER_API_KEY,\n    },\n    customChains: [\n      {\n        network: \"mantle\",\n        chainId: 5000,\n        urls: {\n          apiURL: \"https://explorer.mantle.xyz/api\",\n          browserURL: \"https://explorer.mantle.xyz\",\n        },\n      },\n      {\n        network: \"mantleSepolia\",\n        chainId: 5003,\n        urls: {\n          apiURL: \"https://explorer.sepolia.mantle.xyz/api\",\n          browserURL: \"https://explorer.sepolia.mantle.xyz\",\n        },\n      },\n    ],\n  },\n  solidity: \"0.8.20\",\n};\n```\n\n### Run Verification\n\n```bash\n# Basic verification\nnpx hardhat verify --network mantle <CONTRACT_ADDRESS>\n\n# With constructor arguments\nnpx hardhat verify --network mantle <CONTRACT_ADDRESS> \"arg1\" \"arg2\"\n\n# With constructor arguments file (for complex types)\nnpx hardhat verify --network mantle <CONTRACT_ADDRESS> \\\n  --constructor-args arguments.js\n```\n\n### `arguments.js` for Complex Constructor Args\n\n```javascript\nmodule.exports = [\n  \"0xTokenAddress\",\n  ethers.utils.parseEther(\"1000\"),\n  [\"0xAddr1\", \"0xAddr2\"],\n];\n```\n\n---\n\n## Method 2: Foundry Verification\n\n### `foundry.toml` Configuration\n\n```toml\n[profile.default]\nsrc = \"src\"\nout = \"out\"\nlibs = [\"lib\"]\n\n[rpc_endpoints]\nmantle = \"https://rpc.mantle.xyz\"\nmantle_sepolia = \"https://rpc.sepolia.mantle.xyz\"\n\n[etherscan]\nmantle = { key = \"${MANTLE_EXPLORER_API_KEY}\", url = \"https://explorer.mantle.xyz/api\" }\nmantle_sepolia = { key = \"${MANTLE_EXPLORER_API_KEY}\", url = \"https://explorer.sepolia.mantle.xyz/api\" }\n```\n\n### Verify Command\n\n```bash\n# Standard verification\nforge verify-contract \\\n  --chain-id 5000 \\\n  --compiler-version", "with_skill_answer": "# Mantle Contract Verification on Explorer\n\n## Prerequisites (Confirm Before Proceeding)\n\nBefore verification can begin, the following must be confirmed:\n\n**1. Environment & Chain ID**\n- **Mainnet**: Chain ID `5000` → [explorer.mantle.xyz](https://explorer.mantle.xyz)\n- **Testnet (Sepolia)**: Chain ID `5003` → [sepolia.explorer.mantle.xyz](https://sepolia.explorer.mantle.xyz)\n\n> ⚠️ You must confirm your target environment before proceeding with any verification steps.\n\n---\n\n## Verification Checklist\n\n### Step 1 — Gather Required Artifacts\nEnsure the following are available **from the completed external deployment**:\n\n| Item | Details |\n|---|---|\n| Deployed contract address | From the deployment receipt |\n| Exact Solidity compiler version | Must match what was used to compile |\n| Optimization settings | Enabled/disabled + number of runs |\n| Constructor arguments | ABI-encoded, if applicable |\n| Flattened source or Standard JSON input | Depending on verification method |\n| Compile hash / artifact hash | To confirm no changes since approval |\n\n---\n\n### Step 2 — Choose Verification Method\n\n**Option A: Explorer UI (Manual)**\n1. Navigate to the deployed contract address on the correct explorer\n2. Select **\"Verify & Publish\"**\n3. Choose input type: *Solidity (Single file)*, *Standard JSON*, or *Vyper*\n4. Fill in compiler version, optimization settings, and constructor args\n5. Submit — **this action must be performed by the user/signer externally**\n\n**Option B: Hardhat Verify Plugin**\n```bash\nnpx hardhat verify --network mantle \\\n  <DEPLOYED_CONTRACT_ADDRESS> \\\n  <CONSTRUCTOR_ARG_1> <CONSTRUCTOR_ARG_2>\n```\n> Ensure `hardhat.config` has the correct Mantle network RPC and chain ID configured.\n\n**Option C: Foundry (`forge verify-contract`)**\n```bash\nforge verify-contract <DEPLOYED_CONTRACT_ADDRESS> \\\n  src/YourContract.sol:YourContract \\\n  --chain-id 5000 \\\n  --compiler-version <vX.X.X> \\\n  --constructor-args <ABI_ENCODED_ARGS> \\\n  --verifier-url https://explorer.mantle.xyz/api\n```\n\n---\n\n### Step 3 — Confirm Verification Success\n\n✅ Verification should only be considered successful when:\n- The explorer shows a **\"Contract Verified\"** badge on the contract page\n- The **\"Code\" tab** displays the readable source code\n- There is **explicit explorer response evidence** — do not assume success without this confirmation\n\n> ⚠️ This agent will **never claim verification success** without confirmed explorer response evidence.\n\n---\n\n## Common Failure Reasons\n\n| Issue | Resolution |\n|---|---|\n| Compiler version mismatch | Use exact version (e.g., `v0.8.20+commit.a1b79de6`) |\n| Optimization mismatch | Match runs count precisely (commonly `200`) |\n| Wrong constructor args | Re-encode using ABI encoder |\n| Compile hash changed | Restart pre-deploy checks from scratch |\n| Wrong chain ID submitted | Re-confirm environment and resubmit |\n\n---\n\n## Important Rem", "skill_found": true, "question_id": "MANTLE-Q55", "category": "Mantle", "skill_id": "mantle/mantle-smart-contract-deployer", "ground_truth": "Prepare a verification payload for the explorer API or UI submission. Use exact compiler version, optimizer settings, and constructor arguments. Poll for verification success or failure and record the verification link or identifier. Compiler, optimizer, constructor-arg, and metadata or library mismatches are common failure cases.", "question_text": "How should a Mantle contract be verified on the explorer after external deployment?", "provider": "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6"}
