{"bare_answer": "Based on Mantle's architecture and deployment process, the **initialization phase** (or **pre-deployment setup**) should be complete before the deployer skill takes over for a Mantle contract.\n\nSpecifically, this typically means:\n\n- **Contract configuration and parameters** should be finalized\n- **Constructor arguments** should be prepared\n- **Dependencies and libraries** should be resolved\n- **Compilation** of the contract should be successfully completed\n- **Verification of bytecode/artifacts** should be done\n\nCould you provide more context about the specific framework, documentation, or system you're referring to? The term \"deployer skill\" and \"Mantle contract\" could relate to:\n\n1. **Mantle Network** (L2 blockchain)\n2. A specific **deployment framework or tool**\n3. An **AI agent/skill-based system** for contract deployment\n\nWith more context, I can give you a more precise and accurate answer.", "with_skill_answer": "## Prerequisites Before the Deployer Skill Takes Over\n\nThe deployer skill begins **after** contract design and implementation are fully finalized. Here is what must be complete before handoff:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Contract Authoring & Architecture\n- All Solidity source files are written and finalized\n- Contract design decisions (inheritance, patterns, standards) are locked\n- No open questions about contract logic or structure remain\n- *(If anything here is incomplete → redirect to `$mantle-smart-contract-developer` and OpenZeppelin MCP)*\n\n---\n\n### 2. Compilation & Build Artifacts\n- Contract compiles **without errors or warnings**\n- ABI and bytecode artifacts are generated and saved\n- Compiler version, optimization settings, and runs count are recorded\n- The **compile hash is stable** — any change after this point requires restarting pre-deploy checks\n\n---\n\n### 3. Constructor Arguments\n- **Every constructor parameter has an explicit, confirmed value**\n- No ambiguity, placeholders, or uncertainty about any argument\n- Argument types match the ABI exactly (addresses checksummed, integers sized correctly, etc.)\n\n---\n\n### 4. Environment & Network Confirmation\n- Target network is explicitly confirmed (**Mantle Mainnet or Mantle Sepolia Testnet**)\n- **Chain ID is verified** (Mantle Mainnet: `5000`, Mantle Sepolia: `5003`)\n- RPC endpoint is identified and accessible\n- Deployer wallet address is known and funded with sufficient **MNT** for gas\n\n---\n\n### 5. Security & Review\n- Code review and/or audit findings are resolved\n- No unresolved TODOs or placeholder logic in the codebase\n- Access control roles and ownership addresses are decided\n\n---\n\n### 6. Signer Readiness\n- The external signer (wallet, hardware device, or multisig) is identified\n- The signer has access to the deployer private key or signing mechanism\n- *(Remember: the deployer skill is read-only — all actual signing and broadcasting happens externally)*\n\n---\n\n### Summary Checklist\n\n| Area | Status Required |\n|---|---|\n| Contract code | Finalized, no changes pending |\n| Compilation | Clean build, artifacts saved |\n| Constructor args | All values explicit and confirmed |\n| Chain ID / network | Confirmed and verified |\n| Wallet / gas | Funded deployer address ready |\n| Security review | All findings resolved |\n| Signer handoff | External signer identified |\n\nOnce **all of the above are satisfied**, the deployer skill can begin deployment-readiness checks, signer handoff preparation, receipt capture planning, and explorer verification readiness.", "skill_found": true, "question_id": "MANTLE-Q59", "category": "Mantle", "skill_id": "mantle/mantle-smart-contract-deployer", "ground_truth": "Contract architecture and implementation decisions should already be finalized. The handoff should come from mantle-smart-contract-developer or an equivalent finalized development brief. The deployer skill starts after design and authoring decisions are complete.", "question_text": "What should be complete before the deployer skill takes over for a Mantle contract?", "provider": "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6"}
{"bare_answer": "## Mantle Gas Token Assumption\n\nBefore deploying or operating a contract on Mantle, you must confirm that **MNT (Mantle's native token) is used for gas fees**, not ETH.\n\n### Key Points to Verify:\n\n1. **MNT is the gas token** – Unlike Ethereum L1 and most other L2s (Optimism, Arbitrum) where ETH pays for gas, Mantle uses **MNT** as the native gas token.\n\n2. **Practical implications to confirm:**\n   - Wallets/contracts must hold **MNT**, not ETH, to pay for transaction fees\n   - Any contract logic that assumes `msg.value` or native currency = ETH needs to be reconsidered\n   - Hardcoded gas cost estimations or ETH-denominated fee assumptions will be incorrect\n   - Cross-chain bridges and fee-forwarding contracts must account for MNT denomination\n\n3. **ETH still exists on Mantle** but as a **bridged ERC-20 token**, not the native gas currency\n\n### Why It Matters:\n- Contracts expecting to receive or send native ETH for gas reimbursement will behave unexpectedly\n- Multi-chain deployments copied from Ethereum/Optimism/Arbitrum may have flawed assumptions about the native token\n\n**Always confirm your contract does not conflate \"native token\" with ETH when deploying to Mantle.**", "with_skill_answer": "## MNT as the Gas Token — Required Confirmation\n\nBefore deploying or operating any contract on Mantle, you must confirm:\n\n> **MNT is the native gas token on Mantle, not ETH.**\n\n---\n\n### What This Means in Practice\n\n| Concern | Implication |\n|---|---|\n| **Deployer wallet funding** | The deploying EOA must hold **MNT**, not ETH, to pay deployment gas fees |\n| **Contract operations** | Any on-chain calls (admin actions, keeper bots, relayers) require MNT-funded wallets |\n| **`msg.value` / native-value transfers** | Native value sent in transactions is denominated in **MNT** — contracts that assume ETH semantics for native value will behave incorrectly |\n| **Price/value assumptions** | If a contract uses native token value for pricing, collateral, or fee logic, those figures must be calibrated to MNT, not ETH |\n| **Frontend & offchain services** | Any integration that estimates gas or displays native token balances must reference MNT |\n\n---\n\n### Confirmation Checklist Item\n\nBefore proceeding to the development brief or deployment, explicitly verify:\n\n- [ ] Deployer wallet is funded with **MNT** on the correct environment (`mainnet` or `testnet`)\n- [ ] No contract logic conflates native token with ETH-specific value assumptions\n- [ ] Any hardcoded token addresses for \"wrapped native\" point to the **WMNT** contract, not WETH\n- [ ] Offchain services (gas estimators, monitoring) are configured for MNT denomination\n\n---\n\nThis is a **blocking prerequisite** — it must be resolved before the development brief is finalized and before any handoff to `$mantle-smart-contract-deployer`.", "skill_found": true, "question_id": "MANTLE-Q60", "category": "Mantle", "skill_id": "mantle/mantle-smart-contract-developer", "ground_truth": "Mantle native gas assumptions must use MNT, not ETH.", "question_text": "What gas-token assumption must be confirmed before deploying or operating a contract on Mantle?", "provider": "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6"}
